How long does it take for your towel to dry after you shower? a few hours? a day? a week?
Assume you're drying your feline friend in your previous post here;
First you shake off excessive water while in the shower. this is easy, just shake and "squeegee" yourself with your extremities. This should rid you of 50% water almost instantly.
Second, you ruffle the thickest fur with an absorbant towel and try to create pathways/pockets for water to exit out of. This will rid you of a lot of water, but still leave you moist unfortunetly
Third would be blowdrying and gentle towelling of less dense patches of fur (usually extremities)
Assuming this is done in a decently fast manner drying shouldn't take more than 20-30 minutes.

As for the drains, you can install a sieve-like net under/in the drain that you simply lift up, empty and put back for easy cleaning. It's also inexpensive (and can be self-made if you're broke af)
(If you're worried about condensation and/or humidity while drying, open the bathroom door and a window)
